2x Stout and Strong     </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">BID - 3 or 4... <br />
<br />
START - Legolas, DH and Merry - pull Gimli…<br />
<br />
FP:  You have a goal to reach here - and you should be able to reach it (granted there are 80 cards - but don’t worry almost all are playable within the first few sites)…But you need to get Gandalf out - yes I brought back Friend of the Shirefolk…And with Fury or Mithrandir, Mithrandir (which ever you choose, you can stop Grima, CC for the most part - though conditional)<br />
Dwarves - Power players - play your Conditions as you pull them and try now to discard them in case you do discard them, use Defending the Keep to get them back - simple and succinct.<br />
<br />
Leggy - Don’t worry about Leggy - he’s just there to piss people off…and he does such a good job.<br />
<br />
Gandalf - is Key in defeating Grima CC decks - I haven’t face one yet - but I’m sure this is the way to beat that lil’ fart knocker.<br />
<br />
Shadow - AHHH...Very simple...all of your Rider&#39;s are fierce...MUah hahaha. The only real way to stop these guys is to lay down a ludicrous amount of Archery = impossible.  Saruman is key to keeping your opponent from moving, other then the fact it will be hard to beat down multiple Minions with Vitality of 3 or more.  Tower of Orthanc is there to keep your Wargs moving - makes your opponent think twice about moving even if only one Companion is exhausted.<br />
<br />
Path - is a mixture to help both FP and Shadow.  It should be effective if you don’t go first - but with the ability of the Wargs and your FP you should be able to move quite easily - don’t worry to much about Twilight - you will be well equipped against small minions and with Greatest Kingdom of my People - opponents don’t have a real big shot of drawing things they need for their Goblins or IsenOrcs.<br />
<br />
NEED HELP...hopefully some pointers on Wargs...thanks...  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
